      • lock

        public PacketEventsSettings lock()
        This method locks the settings. If the settings are locked, you won't be able to modify any settings using the setters.

      • backupServerVersion

        @Deprecated
public PacketEventsSettings backupServerVersion(ServerVersion serverVersion)
        Deprecated. Use getFallbackServerVersion()
        This is the server version PacketEvents should assume the server is when detecting the server version fails using the Bukkit API. This seems to be most common on 1.7.10 paper forks. They probably mess up somewhere.

      • compatInjector

        @Deprecated
public PacketEventsSettings compatInjector(boolean compatInjector)
        Deprecated. 
        This decides if PacketEvents should inject users earlier than usual, resulting in us being able to resolve client versions without the need of any dependencies. We end up using a different injection method which isn't supported on a few spigot forks.
        Parameters:
        compatInjector - Value
        Returns:
        Settings instance.
